title: GPT-5 Achieves 95% on SWE-bench Verified
summary: We present GPT-5, a large language model that achieves 95% accuracy on SWE-bench Verified, a significant improvement over previous models. The model demonstrates strong code generation and multi-step reasoning capabilities.

title: OSWorld Benchmark: Scaling OS-Level Task Automation to 10,000 Tasks
summary: We introduce an expanded OSWorld benchmark with 10,000 diverse operating system tasks. Current frontier models achieve 65% success rate, up from 45% six months ago.

title: Algorithmic Efficiency Gains: 10x Compute Reduction via Sparse Attention
summary: We demonstrate a novel sparse attention mechanism that achieves equivalent performance with 10x less compute. This represents approximately 1 OOM improvement in algorithmic efficiency.

title: Red Teaming Large Language Models: New Jailbreak Techniques
summary: We present comprehensive red teaming results for frontier models, identifying 15 new jailbreak techniques that bypass current safety alignment measures.

title: Multi-Day Agentic Tasks: Planning and Execution Over Extended Horizons
summary: We demonstrate an agent capable of planning and executing multi-day software projects, achieving 72% success rate on complex coding tasks spanning 3-5 days.
